{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17645095","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17645095"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:12:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:12:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18083"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18083","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18083"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.04,0.85,0,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10797"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106348"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10797"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18083"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88817"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5763"},{"type":"tags","id":"11382"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25151"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25982"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39187"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106348","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/106348"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with acute respiratory distress. She has a valid advance care directive that clearly states she does not want intubation or mechanical ventilation under any circumstances.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate action regarding the advance care directive?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Override the directive due to the emergency situation","Request family members to authorise intubation","Respect and follow the directive","Delay decision until senior review","Seek legal advice before proceeding"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Erespect and follow the directive\u003C/strong\u003E. Advance care directives are legally binding documents that express a person\u0027s wishes for future medical care when they cannot make or communicate decisions. Healthcare professionals have a legal and ethical obligation to follow valid directives.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther actions would be inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOverride the directive due to the emergency situation\u003C/strong\u003E would violate patient autonomy and is legally indefensible, as advance care directives remain valid in emergencies.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest family members to authorise intubation\u003C/strong\u003E would be inappropriate as family members cannot override a valid advance care directive.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDelay decision until senior review\u003C/strong\u003E risks implementing unwanted interventions and violating the patient\u0027s expressed wishes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESeek legal advice before proceeding\u003C/strong\u003E would cause unnecessary delays when clear instructions already exist.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlternative care should focus on providing the required medical interventions that fall within the accepted scope of the patients advanced care directive and align with the patient\u0027s documented wishes. The directive can only be changed by the patient themselves while they retain decision-making capacity.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Advance care directives are legally binding documents that specify a person\u0027s wishes for future medical care if they lose decision-making capacity.","Healthcare professionals must follow valid advance care directives even if they disagree with the patient\u0027s choices.","Advance care directives can be revoked by a person with decision-making capacity at any time."],"references":["Mandal J, Ponnambath DK, Parija SC. Bioethics: A brief review. Trop Parasitol. 2017;7(1):5-7. doi:10.4103/tp.TP_4_17 Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28459009/","Varkey B. Principles of Clinical Ethics and Their Application to Practice. Med Princ Pract. 2021;30(1):17-28. doi:10.1159/000509119 Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32498071/","Queensland Government. Advance health directive [Internet]. Brisbane: Queensland Government; [cited 2025 Jun 17]. Available from: https://www.qld.gov.au/law/legal-mediation-and-justice-of-the-peace/power-of-attorney-and-making-decisions-for-others/advance-health-directive"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88817"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18083"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"88817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/88817"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-18T12:27:58+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-18T12:29:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10797"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"106348"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"rela